<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 07 at 4:13PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of north central
Fergus, southwestern Blaine and northern Chouteau Counties through
445 PM MDT...
At 413 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 17 miles northwest of Fort Benton to 7 miles
east of Winifred. Movement was east at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Winifred, Loma, Judith Landing, Iliad and Virgelle.
This includes Highway 87 between mile markers 45 and 74.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
